Subject: [PATCH 5/5] arch: arm : config: Increased the size of CMA

To avoid the error in the continous stream from the camera to the
HDMI Display , CMA size is increased from 64 to 128 MB.

Change-Id: Ia2a455d285db2ec9c3ef21c626311ad596f69499
Signed-off-by: Anil Dsouza <anil.dsouza@einfochips.com>
---
 arch/arm/configs/stm32mp1_dhsom_defconfig | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/arch/arm/configs/stm32mp1_dhsom_defconfig b/arch/arm/configs/stm32mp1_dhsom_defconfig
index 5f80a9e83..22522f5de 100644
--- a/arch/arm/configs/stm32mp1_dhsom_defconfig
+++ b/arch/arm/configs/stm32mp1_dhsom_defconfig
@@ -465,7 +465,7 @@ CONFIG_CRYPTO_ZSTD=y
 # CONFIG_CRYPTO_DEV_VIRTIO is not set
 CONFIG_CRC_CCITT=y
 CONFIG_CRC4=y
-CONFIG_CMA_SIZE_MBYTES=64
+CONFIG_CMA_SIZE_MBYTES=128
 CONFIG_PRINTK_TIME=y
 CONFIG_MAGIC_SYSRQ=y
 CONFIG_DEBUG_KERNEL=y
